Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.96,0:00:05.58,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,March 14th is White Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.42,0:00:08.42,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Speaking of White Day...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.42,0:00:10.21,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Ran, did you get one?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.84,0:00:12.97,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,A return gift from Shinichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.76,0:00:17.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you give him that, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.60,0:00:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your handmade Valentine's chocolate!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.22,0:00:21.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rather than giving him...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.14,0:00:25.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's more like he helped himself to it...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.94,0:00:29.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} will give me anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.90,0:00:31.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a White Day return gift!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.69,0:00:33.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if you give out chocolate on Valentine's Day...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.57,0:00:36.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll get return gifts on March 14th?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.78,0:00:39.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, you casually give him chocolate on Valentine's Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.91,0:00:43.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if he returns the favor exactly one month later on March 14th...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.62,0:00:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The jolly bells of blinding romance will resound!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.25,0:00:50.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he doesn't, the footsteps of catastrophe will close in.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.92,0:00:52.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Footsteps of catastrophe!?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.38,0:00:55.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Causing your eyelids to swell and permeating your heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.28,0:00:58.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tear drops serve as a prelude to a wealth of drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.87,0:01:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A White Day with a sour taste...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.53,0:01:02.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall reveal the miraculous trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.56,0:01:04.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.27,0:01:06.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.14,0:01:08.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.36,0:01:17.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sky I saw back the gave me a flashback For an instant, I felt you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.36,0:01:25.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Despite my heart nearly being shuttered, your face kept popping up in the sunset
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.16,0:01:33.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why why why Though I already knew I couldn't say it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.17,0:01:40.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lie lie I want you to stay with me I want your love
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.76,0:01:45.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tear drops Isn't that right? You noticed it, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.85,0:01:49.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tear drops Isn't that right? I'm crying, am I not?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.65,0:01:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tear drops Isn't that right? I can never forget our love
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.65,0:01:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tear drops tear drops Solve this mystery tear drops
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.49,0:02:06.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Overflowing with tears I think I've become a little more honest with myself
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.66,0:02:12.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To the starry night, I say: "I believe, forever my dream"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.88,0:02:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quietly my tear drops
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.13,0:02:21.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tear drops Isn't that right? You noticed it, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.01,0:02:24.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tear drops Isn't that right? I'm crying, am I not?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.35,0:02:29.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tear drops Isn't that right? This is my last love
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.23,0:02:32.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,tear drops tear drops It's only for you that my tear drops
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.33,0:02:54.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were invited to Urai Confection's 8th Anniversay party.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.30,0:03:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the company's commemorative party each year,\NPresident Urai Would showcase his magic tricks and skits.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.38,0:03:04.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of the guests were looking forward\Nto his performance for the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.43,0:03:10.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that moment President Urai let out a groan and collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.94,0:03:15.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We thought at first he was doing a mystery skit this year, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.23,0:03:17.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The president actually had ceased breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.19,0:03:22.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was determined to be death by cyanide poisoning, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.86,0:03:25.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Standing closest to the president was his wife, Hoshie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.99,0:03:30.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was reading Ran's palm at the time, making it seem\Nimpossible for her to have administered the poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.16,0:03:35.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police found a bottle containing poison\Nand medicinal wafers in the president's car.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.92,0:03:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the fact that Hoshie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} proposed\Na divorce and corporate spin-off...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.59,0:03:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A suicide prompted by depression was considered.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.99,0:03:45.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.60,0:03:53.23,Signs,,0,0,0,,WHITE DAY OF BETRAYAL
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.58,0:03:53.23,Signs,,0,0,0,,(PART TWO)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.35,0:03:56.65,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Urai Confections 8th Anniversary Party
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.06,0:03:55.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, ma'am...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.31,0:03:58.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think you'd better call the restaurant soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.11,0:04:06.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you and the president only had things to\Ndrink during the part and didn't eat anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.41,0:04:11.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must have dinner reservations at\Nsome expensive restaurant, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.62,0:04:13.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't have any reservations like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.71,0:04:19.02,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Urai Hoshie (49)\NUrai Taruto's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.96,0:04:17.83,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,To get my husband's metabolism going, he\Nwas prohibited from eating out at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.84,0:04:21.05,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's why I made healthy dishes for him every day instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.34,0:04:24.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.05,0:04:26.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what dish did you make for tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.80,0:04:31.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see, what was it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.02,0:04:33.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This party would've been over around 9:00 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.81,0:04:37.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if you saw your guests off, it'd be even later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.52,0:04:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you should've already bought the ingredients, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.48,0:04:45.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, it couldn't be that you knew things\Nwould turn out like this from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.99,0:04:47.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.45,0:04:50.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's with... this child?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.08,0:04:56.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt this person is the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.92,0:05:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did she administer the poison?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.80,0:05:06.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the president collapsed, I remember her\Nhaving both her hands occupied reading Ran's palm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.09,0:05:08.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she had employed a trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.76,0:05:12.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be with that phrase of "Are you still listening?".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.72,0:05:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what could she make him do with that lone phrase?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.90,0:05:21.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's up, Chiba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.38,0:05:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hay fever?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.48,0:05:26.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I took some medicine but it doesn't seem to be effective...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.78,0:05:30.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if I take too much, I'll get drowsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.12,0:05:31.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,kiku\N"Effective"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.79,0:05:38.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I do wish there were some miraculous allergy\Nmedicine that wouldn't make you drowsy...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.13,0:05:40.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Miracle"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.75,0:05:46.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have them confirm the relevance between the poison\Nfound in the victim's car and the medicinal wafers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.01,0:05:46.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.01,0:05:47.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.93,0:05:50.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad's cigarette is on the table!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.35,0:05:52.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.31,0:05:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's burning the napkin!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.81,0:05:57.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But hey, it's a good thing it didn't catch fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.79,0:05:58.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.15,0:06:03.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall correctly, that napkin was under the wife's iced lemon tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.90,0:06:06.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.74,0:06:10.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why she purposely walked over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.20,0:06:13.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.70,0:06:18.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you help me find something that Uncle Kogorou wants?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.54,0:06:21.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this he's looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.92,0:06:26.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said it's evidence of a miraculous\Ntrick that the culprit tried to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.30,0:06:37.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My husband's cause of death was acute\Nmedicinal poisoning due to cyanide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.60,0:06:40.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it seemed only I was able to administer the poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.90,0:06:45.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But at that time, I was holding Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s left hand\Nwith my both hands and reading her palm...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.27,0:06:49.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was impossible for me to have poisoned him manually.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.11,0:06:54.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, a container of cyanide and medicinal wafers\Nwere found in the glove compartment of my husband's car.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.70,0:07:00.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Combined with the fact that those same wafers were\Nfound stuck between my husband's rear teeth...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.58,0:07:03.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can only believe that my husband\Npacked poison inside the wafer...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.46,0:07:06.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And put it in his mouth during the part to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.30,0:07:09.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No other possibilities, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.92,0:07:10.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.51,0:07:16.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then would you please hurry up\Nand release the guests of my party?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.85,0:07:19.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since even my suspicion has been cleared.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.81,0:07:22.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention if I were the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.60,0:07:28.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have invited the great detective Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nto this party that would end up as a murder scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.69,0:07:30.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.99,0:07:33.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if that was part of a strategy you employed...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.16,0:07:37.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be a different story!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.66,0:07:39.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.45,0:07:41.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That wasn't me just now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.56,0:07:43.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.87,0:07:46.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After my voice comes from somewhere else...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.59,0:07:48.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's always a prickling sensation on my neck...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.76,0:07:55.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, sometimes it's the forehead...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.93,0:08:00.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, could it be you've finally got it like usual?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.47,0:08:02.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.35,0:08:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you mean by "strategy"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.02,0:08:07.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.27,0:08:10.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A strategy devised in order for the murder trick to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.65,0:08:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that Hoshie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} could poison her husband, President Urai!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.91,0:08:27.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By strategy, are you saying that I used you, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.04,0:08:28.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.25,0:08:34.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though the one you really used was my\Ndaughter Ran, who I brought with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.88,0:08:39.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If my daughter had testified that both of your hands\Nhad been occupied with reading her palm...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.85,0:08:43.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that after the president collapsed he was unable to move...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.52,0:08:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would believe her over anyone else, and\Nyou would be removed from suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.07,0:08:53.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason why you committed the crime during my speech...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.03,0:08:59.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was so that I vvouldn't be able to see through your\Ntrick by having me at a distance such as on stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.03,0:09:02.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what is this trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.87,0:09:05.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just what are you saying that I could have done at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.00,0:09:08.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said something to your husband, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.75,0:09:10.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,chanto kiiteru\NAre you still listening?"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.21,0:09:13.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I said, that's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.09,0:09:18.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The president loved being showy and would\Ndo things such as magic tricks or skits...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.05,0:09:20.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he couldn't stand sour things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.60,0:09:25.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you proposed this to the president beforehand, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.27,0:09:34.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saying, "Everyone would be surprised if you ate the sour Spy\NChoco White without making a face!" or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.36,0:09:37.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's absurd.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.53,0:09:42.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a few days ago, my husband ate a sour-\Nflavored cake and was bedridden as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.70,0:09:45.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way he'd eat that chocolate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.33,0:09:47.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.83,0:09:50.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By using a miraculous trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.47,0:09:59.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A miraculous trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.72,0:10:03.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know what a "miracle fruit" is, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.35,0:10:05.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.93,0:10:08.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a berry that makes sour things taste sweet when consumed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.52,0:10:11.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was pretty popular a few years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.94,0:10:15.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a small, red berry native to Western Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.86,0:10:20.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One that temporarily changes the\Nperception of sourness to sweetness...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.03,0:10:23.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It consists of miraculin, a suger protein\Nthat acts on one's gustatory organ.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.16,0:10:24.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is indeed a miraculous berry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.62,0:10:30.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If thoroughly rolled on the tongue, the\Neffects will last for an hour or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.50,0:10:35.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why, having had the president eat the\Nberry in advance, the wife asked him this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.09,0:10:40.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In regard to the miracle fruit, "Is it still effective?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.80,0:10:43.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could it be that the poison was...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.68,0:10:44.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.60,0:10:48.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At that time, of the things on the table...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.35,0:10:54.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The most suitable food for testing its effectiveness was\Nthe lemon on the glass of iced tea his wife was drinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.82,0:10:59.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had prepared a piece of lemon\Nby removing one of the wedges...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.61,0:11:04.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And inserted a medicinal wafer filled with poison in its place.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.37,0:11:09.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way when the president put it in his\Nmouth, the poison would be released.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.29,0:11:15.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In short, the wife wrapped the lemon with poison in something...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.42,0:11:17.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And brought it to the party on her person.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.17,0:11:22.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She then swapped the poisoned lemon\Nwith the one on her iced tea...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.26,0:11:25.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hid the original one on her tea in the paper napkin...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.35,0:11:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And waited until my speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.85,0:11:32.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later, from the mouth of the president who had collapsed\Nby ingesting the poison following her question...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.77,0:11:35.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She guickly removed the poisoned lemon and hid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.90,0:11:39.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And by the time everyone was focusing on the president...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.44,0:11:45.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She returned the original lemon that had been\Nwrapped in the napkin back to her glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.91,0:11:50.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having done that, even when the police\Ncame and investigated later...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.12,0:11:53.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They wouldn't find any poison on top of the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.42,0:12:01.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Incidentally, the reason you purposely took a glass from\Nthe third row when you got your iced tea earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.80,0:12:06.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was because you wanted to get a glass that had\Na lemon of similar size to the poisoned one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.01,0:12:08.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.48,0:12:16.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected of a great detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.36,0:12:18.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You notice even the smallest details.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.48,0:12:22.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the reason I chose that glass was just out of habit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.45,0:12:24.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you sometimes do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.24,0:12:28.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead of taking the foremost item, you\Nreach for one in the back without realizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.62,0:12:30.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.99,0:12:33.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I definitely do the same when I buy milk from convenience stores.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.62,0:12:38.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, if my husband had taken the lemon\Nfrom my glass and put it in his mouth...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.34,0:12:40.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think someone definitely would have noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.00,0:12:43.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no one would've seen him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.97,0:12:48.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The president himself would've taken precautions\Nto ensure that no one noticed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.56,0:12:56.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since if he had been seen eating sour food with ease,\Nhe would've been unable to surprise everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.48,0:13:02.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, regarding the evidence of you having\Nhidden the original lemon in a paper napkin...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.11,0:13:04.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forensics has already secured it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.28,0:13:11.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the same paper napkin that I burned on\Npurpose by flinging my cigarette on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.08,0:13:14.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forensics!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.04,0:13:15.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.79,0:13:17.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes sir, this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.33,0:13:21.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please take a close look at that napkin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.63,0:13:26.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The burn mark that stretches straight out turns\Ninto a circular curve mid-way, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.68,0:13:29.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's proof that the lemon was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.89,0:13:33.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's how heat-fixed invisible ink works —\Nonly that part of the paper is easy to burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.18,0:13:38.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, where's the lemon that had the poison prepared in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.48,0:13:42.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I gave the wife a body search, but didn't find any lemons on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.48,0:13:43.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.36,0:13:49.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She took the poisoned lemon from the fallen\Npresident's mouth and temporarily hid it in her shoe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.62,0:13:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when she walked by the table with the glasses\Nlined up in order to undergo the body search...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.12,0:13:59.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She deliberately knocked over the glasses of iced tea on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.88,0:14:06.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By feigning an ankle sprain, she took the poisoned\Nlemon from her shoe and mixed it in with the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.80,0:14:07.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.93,0:14:10.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, go retrieve that lemon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.34,0:14:10.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.97,0:14:11.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No need.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.89,0:14:15.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} reguested it earlier, and we already found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.18,0:14:20.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lemon with a missing wedge and a\Nminute reaction to hydrocyanic acid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.48,0:14:26.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the traces of the president's saliva and both his and\Nthe wife's fingerprints are found on this lemon...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.57,0:14:28.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be conclusive evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.74,0:14:29.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.41,0:14:37.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was because of a grudge regarding sourness that I used a lemon...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.21,0:14:40.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it had indeed turned out to be a failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.46,0:14:42.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it's difficult to hide it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.42,0:14:45.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A grudge regarding sourness?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.50,0:14:46.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.76,0:14:50.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I met my husband at a confectionery school.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.43,0:14:53.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was a teacher and I was a student.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.39,0:14:57.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One day a few years into my studies...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.10,0:15:01.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two people were chosen from the school\Nto compete in a confectionery contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.98,0:15:04.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was one of the two chosen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.90,0:15:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, there was a clear winner before the contest was even held.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.44,0:15:12.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it was obvious that the other guy chosen\Nfrom the school —\hmy boyfriend —\hwould win.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.20,0:15:17.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sour sweets that my boyfriend made were the absolute best.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.16,0:15:21.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So much so that even scouts from famous\Noverseas shops came to recruit him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.50,0:15:22.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In spite of this...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.00,0:15:29.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one could have thought that he'd\Ncommit suicide the day before the contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.43,0:15:35.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time, I thought he was troubled by\Nvarious things having to do with his genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.97,0:15:39.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I psyched myself up and won the\Ncompetition myself in memory of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.35,0:15:43.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, about the "I took second" you said earlier...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.17,0:15:44.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.27,0:15:47.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since if he had competed, I never would have won.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.40,0:15:49.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And a few years later...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.19,0:15:55.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I married my husband, who had been overjoyed at my victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.20,0:15:59.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Precisely that man who drove my boyfriend to his death!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.58,0:16:01.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Drove him to his death?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.17,0:16:09.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My husband confessed to me when he became\Nbedridden from eating the sour cake the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.21,0:16:12.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His becoming aversive to sourness was\Nbecause it reminded him of my ex.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.55,0:16:18.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had eaten a pie my boyfriend had made before the contest...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.68,0:16:20.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And my husband said to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.22,0:16:22.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is too sour.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.93,0:16:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is your tongue stil working?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.98,0:16:25.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.02,0:16:32.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My boyfriend, who had completely trusted my\Nhusband, became neurotic and took his own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.57,0:16:35.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My husband told me this in tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.11,0:16:41.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That he had said that so I could win, and that he\Nnever thought it would result with his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.46,0:16:48.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not knowing just how much...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.88,0:16:52.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How much my boyfriend and I loved each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.81,0:17:03.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected of Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.48,0:17:07.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who would've guessed you flung that cigarette on purpose!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.02,0:17:09.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.69,0:17:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.61,0:17:17.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, since today is White Day, I just felt I\Nwas able to clearly discern black from white!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.20,0:17:18.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,White Day...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.78,0:17:21.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd better contact Midori just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.67,0:17:29.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Midori?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.67,0:17:30.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.59,0:17:34.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, if it isn't the demon inspector\Nwho loves cases more than his wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.42,0:17:37.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what a calling me for?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.43,0:17:39.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't tell me you're drunk!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.18,0:17:43.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There ain't no reason I shouldn't be drunk!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.56,0:17:44.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You stupid octopus!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.40,0:17:48.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.15,0:17:50.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, listen up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.98,0:17:53.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the cupboard next to the fridge, second shelf from the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.20,0:18:02.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd intended to give it to you after I got home,\Nbut it seems I'll be home late tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.70,0:18:07.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, just something to express my feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.41,0:18:08.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.42,0:18:11.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, also...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.71,0:18:14.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't have anything to eat for lunch or dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.55,0:18:16.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I'm counting on you for a feast!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.51,0:18:17.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suuure!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.41,0:18:24.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.64,0:18:28.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess I'll have to go and assist in the police questioning now, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.69,0:18:30.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ask Takagi to take you guys home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.65,0:18:33.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And on your way back...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.98,0:18:37.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop by Eri's and drop this off.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.70,0:18:40.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.74,0:18:42.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A White Day present?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.32,0:18:44.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't get the wrong idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.53,0:18:48.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just don't want the biscuits that I didn't\Nget to give Youko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} to go to waste!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.83,0:18:49.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure, sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.50,0:18:54.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The wrapping's obviously different\Nfrom the one for Youko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.01,0:19:00.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aunt Eri didn't seem happy, did she?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.93,0:19:03.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seemed as if her face was twitching...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.47,0:19:04.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.89,0:19:06.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the face she makes when she tries to hold back a smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.43,0:19:09.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's proof that she's actually overjoyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.48,0:19:12.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then there's Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} over here...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.50,0:19:15.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah-le?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.73,0:19:18.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've somehow completely forgotten the streets in this area!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.82,0:19:20.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't you just check the GPS?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.61,0:19:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.61,0:19:26.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The GPS in this car has been acting up recently...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.08,0:19:29.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess there's no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.95,0:19:31.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll look at the map and direct you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.00,0:19:34.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What district was the Mouri Detective Agency in again?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.88,0:19:36.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the 5th District...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.17,0:19:38.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a bother...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.88,0:19:44.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.39,0:19:46.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,White Day secured!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.26,0:19:46.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.93,0:19:50.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At least look in the glove compartment\Nof your own car once in a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.18,0:19:53.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I put that in there three days ago you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.40,0:19:59.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Satou sure was happy, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.48,0:20:00.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.40,0:20:03.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm, look, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.24,0:20:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.53,0:20:10.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way Shinichi would pay\Nattention to something like White Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.29,0:20:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can just have a long phone call\Nwith Sonoko and forget all about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.96,0:20:20.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An e-mail from Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.71,0:20:21.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What can it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.30,0:20:27.76,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I got a White Day return gift from Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.76,0:20:31.14,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He said he got a white star mark of victory just for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.15,0:20:36.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.56,0:20:37.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.36,0:20:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Calling Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.61,0:20:43.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't such a good idea anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.97,0:21:13.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rain lasted almost forever
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.98,0:21:22.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although we have a moon so blue, I still await the shining sun
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.57,0:21:24.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,open my eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.78,0:21:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,「My wish」 I'm a bit tired of trying to live tough
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.82,0:21:32.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,「Deliver」 My cloudy path is still long
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.83,0:21:36.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,「Deeper」 I wish for it to keep radiating under the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.83,0:21:40.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,「Stronger」 With your praying voice, it should all clear up
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.75,0:21:45.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I want to meet you" Nothing other than that is my true answer
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.72,0:21:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shout as many times as needed! If I paint my dream alone in the sky with a full moon
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.81,0:22:02.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you can see it too (full moon night crisis)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.73,0:22:10.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you can see it too (I want to meet you)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.08,0:22:22.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah-le-le!?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.42,0:22:26.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something in the door's mail slot!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.05,0:22:29.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was this here when we left?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.66,0:22:31.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.93,0:22:32.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.69,0:22:43.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No reason it'd be from him...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.28,0:22:47.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.24,0:22:49.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A notice of deficiency?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.82,0:22:53.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I recall, the deadline to file a confirmed tax return is March 15th...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.12,0:22:55.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.12,0:22:56.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.08,0:23:01.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cough drops?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.50,0:23:03.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.46,0:23:08.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had a nasally voice the last time I talked with you on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.17,0:23:10.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Try these and get well soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.63,0:23:12.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,White Day.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.97,0:23:17.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to say that I didn't have any expectations...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.93,0:23:20.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now that I've gotten a return gift...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.77,0:23:22.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must mean that my feelings have been received.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.95,0:23:35.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.71,0:23:44.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Makoto{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.34,0:23:46.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.84,0:23:49.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm in the middle of a champion interview...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.13,0:23:52.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you won't be giving me White Day\Nmarshmallows or anything at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.22,0:23:54.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll get to it soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.18,0:23:59.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though it's White Day, it can give you a black eye...
